  "label": "Brined Chicken",
  "notes": "Do not shortcut the brining and resting times. I always omit the sugar and vary the ingredients here based on what's available. If you're going to get creative with the ingredients to flavor the chicken, be heavy-handed. I've substituted some of the water for beer and wine (not together obviously) and not seen a perceivable difference in the flavor of the chicken. In fact, the thing that seems to influence the flavor of the chicken the most is the quality of your chicken.",
